content: Correct, "次元を超越した" does not have to be specifically about dimensionality. It is a figurative phrase used to convey the idea of something or someone surpassing or exceeding the boundaries or limitations of their respective field or category. It can be used to describe a wide range of things such as a person's abilities, a work of art, technology, etc. The phrase is often used to express admiration or awe for something that is considered to be exceptional or extraordinary.
